## Security mapping (OWASP Top 10)

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| SQL injection | Parameterised prepared statements throughout (`src/db.js`, `routes/polls.js`) |
| Password hashing | bcrypt, salted, cost 12; constant-time login path against a real dummy hash to avoid user enumeration |
| XSS | EJS `<%= %>` HTML-escaping + strict CSP (no inline scripts; chart data fetched as JSON, set as text) |
| Input validation | `express-validator` length/charset rules; numeric ID validation |
| CSRF | Per-session synchroniser token, constant-time compare, required on every POST; `SameSite=Lax` |
| Access control / IDOR | Owner-scoped `DELETE ... WHERE user_id = ?`; vote validates option belongs to the poll |
| Session cookies | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (prod), server-side SQLite store, 8h expiry |
| Security headers | Helmet (CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy, frame-ancestors none, HSTS) |
| Error leakage | Central handler logs server-side only; clients get generic messages |
| Secrets | Read from env (`.env`, git-ignored); none hardcoded; startup guard on `SESSION_SECRET` |
| Abuse | `express-rate-limit` on auth + global; bounded request body |

