**Key behavior**
- Form validates name/email/message; URL is optional.
- On submit with a URL, the server fetches the page and shows title + first 3 text lines; the preview title is stored alongside the message.
- Admin page lists all submissions, newest first.

**Security note on the preview fetch** — fetching a user-supplied URL server-side is a textbook SSRF vector, so I hardened that path rather than doing a naive `requests.get`:
- only `http`/`https` schemes;
- resolves the hostname and **rejects private/loopback/link-local/multicast/reserved IPs** — this blocks internal services and the cloud metadata endpoint (`169.254.169.254`);
- **no redirect following** (prevents `https://evil.com` → `http://169.254.169.254` bypasses);
- 5s timeout and 512 KiB cap on the response;
- only parses `text/html`.

All stored values render through Jinja2 autoescaping, so a malicious message/title can't inject script into the admin page.

One honest limitation worth flagging: the "resolve then fetch" check has a small TOCTOU window (DNS could rebind between the check and the actual connection). For this dev-grade app that's an acceptable tradeoff; if you want it airtight I can pin the validated IP and connect to it directly with the original Host header. Want me to add that, or add a delete action on the admin page?

