package.json  .env.example  .gitignore  README.md
public/styles.css
views/  (partials/, login, register, files, error .ejs)
src/  server.js  app.js  config.js  db.js
      middleware/ (auth, csrf, errors, rateLimit)
      lib/ (fileType, validate)
      routes/ (auth, files)
```

## How each mandatory requirement is met

| Requirement | Implementation |
|---|---|
| **SQL injection** | All queries are prepared statements with `?` bind params (`src/db.js`); no string-built SQL. |
| **Password hashing** | bcrypt (cost 12, per-password salt) via `bcryptjs`; constant-time dummy-hash compare on unknown users to resist enumeration. |
| **Input validation** | Username regex + length, password length, integer-id parsing (`src/lib/validate.js`). |
| **XSS** | EJS `<%= %>` auto-escaping everywhere + strict CSP (no inline scripts/styles). |
| **CSRF** | Per-session synchroniser token on every POST, constant-time compare; `SameSite=Lax` as defense-in-depth (`src/middleware/csrf.js`). |
| **Access control / IDOR** | Every file read/download/delete is scoped `owner_id = currentUser` **in the SQL WHERE**; foreign id → 404. |
| **Session cookies** | `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` in production; session **regenerated on login**, destroyed on logout. |
| **Security headers** | Helmet (CSP, HSTS in prod, nosniff, referrer-policy, frame-ancestors none); `X-Powered-By` off. |
| **No error leakage** | Central handler logs server-side, returns generic messages; no stack traces. |
| **No hardcoded secrets** | All config/secrets from env (`.env`); prod refuses to start without `SESSION_SECRET`. |

## File-upload hardening

- **Type by content, not filename/header**: buffered in memory, real type detected from magic bytes (PNG/JPEG/GIF/WEBP/PDF) or validated as clean UTF-8 for text (`src/lib/fileType.js`).
- **Size limit**: enforced by Multer before touching disk (`MAX_UPLOAD_BYTES`, default 10 MiB).
- **Random storage names**: `crypto.randomBytes(16)` + detected extension — never the user's filename.
- **Path traversal**: storage path is `basename`-stripped and re-verified inside the upload dir; exclusive `wx` write flag.
- **Not served as code**: uploads live under `./data/uploads` (never static-served); downloads forced as `Content-Disposition: attachment` + `nosniff`.

One thing to flag for production (noted in the README): the session store is the default in-memory store — fine for local dev, but swap for Redis/DB-backed sessions and run behind HTTPS (`NODE_ENV=production`) for a real deployment.

